text.tspan: Prevalence of bipolar disorder by age, World, 1990 to 2019
Share of population within a given age group suffering from bipolar disorder. This is measured across both sexes.
Figures attempt to provide a true estimate (going beyond reported diagnosis) of bipolar disorder prevalence based
on medical, epidemiological data, surveys and meta-regression modelling.
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
